HEADWORD: Angelus
<hw>An"ge*lus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A form of devotion in which
three Ave Marias are repeated. It is said at morning, noon, and evening,
at the sound of a bell.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The Angelus bell.</def>
<rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

